{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":515,"text":"I think I was supposed\nto talk about my new book,"},{"time":3000,"text":"which is called \"Blink,\""},{"time":4903,"text":"and it's about snap judgments\nand first impressions."},{"time":8000,"text":"And it comes out in January,\nand I hope you all buy it in triplicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11815,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13313,"text":"But I was thinking about this,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and I realized that although\nmy new book makes me happy,"},{"time":19234,"text":"and I think would make my mother happy,"},{"time":21894,"text":"it's not really about happiness."},{"time":24376,"text":"So I decided instead,\nI would talk about someone"},{"time":28000,"text":"who I think has done as much\nto make Americans happy"},{"time":31703,"text":"as perhaps anyone over the last 20 years,"},{"time":35000,"text":"a man who is a great\npersonal hero of mine:"},{"time":38000,"text":"someone by the name of Howard Moskowitz,"},{"time":41000,"text":"who is most famous\nfor reinventing spaghetti sauce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45323,"text":"Howard's about this high, and he's round,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and he's in his 60s,\nand he has big huge glasses"},{"time":55113,"text":"and thinning gray hair,"},{"time":56930,"text":"and he has a kind of wonderful\nexuberance and vitality,"},{"time":60778,"text":"and he has a parrot,\nand he loves the opera,"},{"time":63810,"text":"and he's a great aficionado\nof medieval history."},{"time":68203,"text":"And by profession, he's a psychophysicist."},{"time":70831,"text":"Now, I should tell you that I have no idea\nwhat psychophysics is,"},{"time":75492,"text":"although at some point in my life,"},{"time":77206,"text":"I dated a girl for two years"},{"time":78676,"text":"who was getting\nher doctorate in psychophysics."},{"time":80940,"text":"Which should tell you something\nabout that relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84508,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86829,"text":"As far as I know, psychophysics\nis about measuring things."},{"time":90000,"text":"And Howard is very interested\nin measuring things."},{"time":92655,"text":"And he graduated\nwith his doctorate from Harvard,"},{"time":95052,"text":"and he set up a little consulting shop\nin White Plains, New York."},{"time":99055,"text":"And one of his first clients was Pepsi."},{"time":101437,"text":"This is many years ago,\nback in the early 70s."},{"time":105444,"text":"And Pepsi came to Howard and they said,"},{"time":107380,"text":"\"You know, there's this new\nthing called aspartame,"},{"time":109802,"text":"and we would like to make Diet Pepsi."},{"time":111710,"text":"We'd like you to figure out"},{"time":113711,"text":"how much aspartame we should put\nin each can of Diet Pepsi"},{"time":117241,"text":"in order to have the perfect drink.\""},{"time":119721,"text":"Now that sounds like an incredibly\nstraightforward question to answer,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and that's what Howard thought."},{"time":125501,"text":"Because Pepsi told him,"},{"time":126826,"text":"\"We're working with a band\nbetween eight and 12 percent."},{"time":129533,"text":"Anything below eight percent\nsweetness is not sweet enough;"},{"time":132476,"text":"anything above 12 percent\nsweetness is too sweet."},{"time":135739,"text":"We want to know: what's the sweet\nspot between 8 and 12?\""},{"time":139372,"text":"Now, if I gave you this problem to do,\nyou would all say, it's very simple."},{"time":143357,"text":"What we do is you make up\na big experimental batch of Pepsi,"},{"time":147000,"text":"at every degree of sweetness --\neight percent, 8.1, 8.2, 8.3,"},{"time":151510,"text":"all the way up to 12 --"},{"time":152815,"text":"and we try this out\nwith thousands of people,"},{"time":155328,"text":"and we plot the results on a curve,"},{"time":157558,"text":"and we take the most popular\nconcentration, right?"},{"time":160563,"text":"Really simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161842,"text":"Howard does the experiment,\nand he gets the data back,"},{"time":164406,"text":"and he plots it on a curve,"},{"time":165771,"text":"and all of a sudden he realizes\nit's not a nice bell curve."},{"time":168659,"text":"In fact, the data doesn't make any sense."},{"time":170637,"text":"It's a mess. It's all over the place."},{"time":173000,"text":"Now, most people in that business,\nin the world of testing food and such,"},{"time":177637,"text":"are not dismayed\nwhen the data comes back a mess."},{"time":180478,"text":"They think, \"Well, you know,"},{"time":181994,"text":"figuring out what people think\nabout cola's not that easy.\""},{"time":184852,"text":"\"You know, maybe we made an error\nsomewhere along the way.\""},{"time":187701,"text":"\"You know, let's just\nmake an educated guess,\""},{"time":189922,"text":"and they simply point\nand they go for 10 percent,"},{"time":192331,"text":"right in the middle."},{"time":194000,"text":"Howard is not so easily placated."},{"time":196000,"text":"Howard is a man of a certain degree\nof intellectual standards."},{"time":198936,"text":"And this was not good enough for him,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and this question bedeviled him for years."},{"time":203306,"text":"And he would think it through\nand say, \"What was wrong?"},{"time":206000,"text":"Why could we not make sense\nof this experiment with Diet Pepsi?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":210360,"text":"And one day, he was sitting\nin a diner in White Plains,"},{"time":213000,"text":"about to go trying to dream up\nsome work for Nescafé."},{"time":216336,"text":"And suddenly, like a bolt of lightning,\nthe answer came to him."},{"time":220153,"text":"And that is, that when they analyzed\nthe Diet Pepsi data,"},{"time":222851,"text":"they were asking the wrong question."},{"time":224597,"text":"They were looking for the perfect Pepsi,"},{"time":226751,"text":"and they should have been\nlooking for the perfect Pepsis."},{"time":230814,"text":"Trust me."},{"time":231849,"text":"This was an enormous revelation."},{"time":234000,"text":"This was one of the most brilliant\nbreakthroughs in all of food science."},{"time":237699,"text":"Howard immediately went on the road,"},{"time":239441,"text":"and he would go to conferences\naround the country,"},{"time":241823,"text":"and he would stand up and say,"},{"time":243405,"text":"\"You had been looking\nfor the perfect Pepsi."},{"time":245492,"text":"You're wrong."},{"time":246746,"text":"You should be looking\nfor the perfect Pepsis.\""},{"time":249857,"text":"And people would look at him\nblankly and say,"},{"time":252317,"text":"\"What are you talking about? Craziness.\""},{"time":254404,"text":"And they would say, \"Move! Next!\""},{"time":256000,"text":"Tried to get business,\nnobody would hire him --"},{"time":258238,"text":"he was obsessed, though,"},{"time":259646,"text":"and he talked about it\nand talked about it."},{"time":261677,"text":"Howard loves the Yiddish expression"},{"time":263494,"text":"\"To a worm in horseradish,\nthe world is horseradish.\""},{"time":266541,"text":"This was his horseradish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268165,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269851,"text":"He was obsessed with it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"And finally, he had a breakthrough."},{"time":274835,"text":"Vlasic Pickles came to him,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and they said, \"Doctor Moskowitz,\nwe want to make the perfect pickle.\""},{"time":281673,"text":"And he said,"},{"time":282721,"text":"\"There is no perfect pickle;\nthere are only perfect pickles.\""},{"time":286331,"text":"And he came back to them and he said,"},{"time":288125,"text":"\"You don't just need\nto improve your regular;"},{"time":290359,"text":"you need to create zesty.\""},{"time":291876,"text":"And that's where we got zesty pickles."},{"time":294516,"text":"Then the next person came to him:\nCampbell's Soup."},{"time":297000,"text":"And this was even more important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299024,"text":"In fact, Campbell's Soup\nis where Howard made his reputation."},{"time":302420,"text":"Campbell's made Prego,"},{"time":303837,"text":"and Prego, in the early 80s,\nwas struggling next to Ragù,"},{"time":307729,"text":"which was the dominant\nspaghetti sauce of the 70s and 80s."},{"time":311546,"text":"In the industry -- I don't\nknow whether you care about this,"},{"time":314413,"text":"or how much time I have to go into this."},{"time":316437,"text":"But it was, technically speaking\n-- this is an aside --"},{"time":319091,"text":"Prego is a better tomato sauce than Ragù."},{"time":321175,"text":"The quality of the tomato paste\nis much better;"},{"time":323480,"text":"the spice mix is far superior;"},{"time":325324,"text":"it adheres to the pasta\nin a much more pleasing way."},{"time":327834,"text":"In fact, they would do\nthe famous bowl test"},{"time":329935,"text":"back in the 70s with Ragù and Prego."},{"time":332604,"text":"You'd have a plate of spaghetti,\nand you would pour it on, right?"},{"time":336460,"text":"And the Ragù would all go to the bottom,\nand the Prego would sit on top."},{"time":341129,"text":"That's called \"adherence.\""},{"time":342684,"text":"And, anyway, despite the fact\nthat they were far superior in adherence,"},{"time":347248,"text":"and the quality of their tomato paste,"},{"time":350043,"text":"Prego was struggling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351436,"text":"So they came to Howard,\nand they said, fix us."},{"time":354811,"text":"And Howard looked\nat their product line, and he said,"},{"time":357334,"text":"what you have is a dead tomato society."},{"time":361183,"text":"So he said, this is what I want to do."},{"time":363389,"text":"And he got together\nwith the Campbell's soup kitchen,"},{"time":365969,"text":"and he made 45 varieties\nof spaghetti sauce."},{"time":369454,"text":"And he varied them according\nto every conceivable way"},{"time":372331,"text":"that you can vary tomato sauce:"},{"time":374000,"text":"by sweetness, by level of garlic,"},{"time":375882,"text":"by tomatoey-ness,\nby tartness, by sourness,"},{"time":379121,"text":"by visible solids --"},{"time":380485,"text":"my favorite term\nin the spaghetti sauce business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383770,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384795,"text":"Every conceivable way\nyou can vary spaghetti sauce,"},{"time":388357,"text":"he varied spaghetti sauce."},{"time":390160,"text":"And then he took this whole raft\nof 45 spaghetti sauces,"},{"time":393917,"text":"and he went on the road."},{"time":395098,"text":"He went to New York, to Chicago,"},{"time":397001,"text":"he went to Jacksonville, to Los Angeles."},{"time":398954,"text":"And he brought in people\nby the truckload into big halls."},{"time":402740,"text":"And he sat them down for two hours,"},{"time":404489,"text":"and over the course of that two hours,\nhe gave them ten bowls."},{"time":407840,"text":"Ten small bowls of pasta,"},{"time":409122,"text":"with a different spaghetti\nsauce on each one."},{"time":412185,"text":"And after they ate each bowl,\nthey had to rate, from 0 to 100,"},{"time":416355,"text":"how good they thought\nthe spaghetti sauce was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419490,"text":"At the end of that process,\nafter doing it for months and months,"},{"time":422585,"text":"he had a mountain of data"},{"time":424152,"text":"about how the American people\nfeel about spaghetti sauce."},{"time":428000,"text":"And then he analyzed the data."},{"time":429491,"text":"Did he look for the most popular\nvariety of spaghetti sauce?"},{"time":433492,"text":"No! Howard doesn't believe\nthat there is such a thing."},{"time":436270,"text":"Instead, he looked\nat the data, and he said,"},{"time":438357,"text":"let's see if we can group all these\ndifferent data points into clusters."},{"time":444000,"text":"Let's see if they congregate\naround certain ideas."},{"time":447000,"text":"And sure enough, if you sit down,"},{"time":449229,"text":"and you analyze all this data\non spaghetti sauce,"},{"time":452818,"text":"you realize that all Americans\nfall into one of three groups."},{"time":456340,"text":"There are people\nwho like their spaghetti sauce plain;"},{"time":459277,"text":"there are people\nwho like their spaghetti sauce spicy;"},{"time":462000,"text":"and there are people\nwho like it extra chunky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464929,"text":"And of those three facts,\nthe third one was the most significant,"},{"time":469000,"text":"because at the time, in the early 1980s,"},{"time":471678,"text":"if you went to a supermarket,"},{"time":473202,"text":"you would not find\nextra-chunky spaghetti sauce."},{"time":476987,"text":"And Prego turned to Howard, and they said,"},{"time":479024,"text":"\"You're telling me\nthat one third of Americans"},{"time":481745,"text":"crave extra-chunky spaghetti sauce"},{"time":485000,"text":"and yet no one is servicing their needs?\""},{"time":487523,"text":"And he said \"Yes!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":488571,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":489887,"text":"And Prego then went back,"},{"time":491253,"text":"and completely reformulated\ntheir spaghetti sauce,"},{"time":493649,"text":"and came out with a line of extra chunky\nthat immediately and completely"},{"time":497327,"text":"took over the spaghetti sauce\nbusiness in this country."},{"time":500335,"text":"And over the next 10 years,\nthey made 600 million dollars"},{"time":504762,"text":"off their line of extra-chunky sauces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"Everyone else in the industry looked\nat what Howard had done, and they said,"},{"time":511514,"text":"\"Oh my god! We've been\nthinking all wrong!\""},{"time":513945,"text":"And that's when you started to get\nseven different kinds of vinegar,"},{"time":517239,"text":"and 14 different kinds of mustard,\nand 71 different kinds of olive oil."},{"time":522729,"text":"And then eventually\neven Ragù hired Howard,"},{"time":526000,"text":"and Howard did the exact same thing\nfor Ragù that he did for Prego."},{"time":529215,"text":"And today, if you go\nto a really good supermarket,"},{"time":531590,"text":"do you know how many Ragùs there are?"},{"time":533757,"text":"36!"},{"time":535967,"text":"In six varieties:"},{"time":537561,"text":"Cheese, Light,"},{"time":540635,"text":"Robusto, Rich &amp; Hearty,"},{"time":543761,"text":"Old World Traditional --"},{"time":547483,"text":"Extra-Chunky Garden."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549224,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":551000,"text":"That's Howard's doing."},{"time":552768,"text":"That is Howard's gift\nto the American people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555000,"text":"Now why is that important?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":556705,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"It is, in fact, enormously important."},{"time":561105,"text":"I'll explain to you why."},{"time":562499,"text":"What Howard did is he fundamentally\nchanged the way the food industry thinks"},{"time":566644,"text":"about making you happy."},{"time":569000,"text":"Assumption number one\nin the food industry used to be"},{"time":572000,"text":"that the way to find out\nwhat people want to eat,"},{"time":574724,"text":"what will make people happy,\nis to ask them."},{"time":577628,"text":"And for years and years and years,"},{"time":579310,"text":"Ragù and Prego would have focus groups,"},{"time":581572,"text":"and they would sit you down,\nand they would say,"},{"time":584056,"text":"\"What do you want in a spaghetti sauce?"},{"time":585953,"text":"Tell us what you want\nin a spaghetti sauce.\""},{"time":588052,"text":"And for all those years -- 20, 30 years --"},{"time":591000,"text":"through all those focus group sessions,"},{"time":593000,"text":"no one ever said they wanted extra-chunky."},{"time":596754,"text":"Even though at least a third of them,\ndeep in their hearts, actually did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600229,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602696,"text":"People don't know what they want!"},{"time":604732,"text":"As Howard loves to say,"},{"time":606202,"text":"\"The mind knows not\nwhat the tongue wants.\""},{"time":608978,"text":"It's a mystery!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":610154,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":611182,"text":"And a critically important step"},{"time":613612,"text":"in understanding\nour own desires and tastes"},{"time":616967,"text":"is to realize that we cannot always\nexplain what we want, deep down."},{"time":621242,"text":"If I asked all of you, for example,\nin this room, what you want in a coffee,"},{"time":625302,"text":"you know what you'd say?"},{"time":626654,"text":"Every one of you would say,\n\"I want a dark, rich, hearty roast.\""},{"time":631555,"text":"It's what people always say\nwhen you ask them."},{"time":633737,"text":"\"What do you like?\"\n\"Dark, rich, hearty roast!\""},{"time":636293,"text":"What percentage of you actually\nlike a dark, rich, hearty roast?"},{"time":639830,"text":"According to Howard, somewhere\nbetween 25 and 27 percent of you."},{"time":643567,"text":"Most of you like milky, weak coffee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645786,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":646811,"text":"But you will never, ever say\nto someone who asks you what you want"},{"time":650167,"text":"that \"I want a milky, weak coffee.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":652382,"text":"So that's number one thing\nthat Howard did."},{"time":656528,"text":"Number two thing that Howard did\nis he made us realize --"},{"time":660000,"text":"it's another very critical point --"},{"time":662000,"text":"he made us realize the importance"},{"time":664198,"text":"of what he likes to call\n\"horizontal segmentation.\""},{"time":668000,"text":"Why is this critical?"},{"time":669039,"text":"Because this is the way the food industry\nthought before Howard."},{"time":672761,"text":"What were they obsessed with\nin the early 80s?"},{"time":675095,"text":"They were obsessed with mustard."},{"time":676659,"text":"In particular, they were obsessed\nwith the story of Grey Poupon."},{"time":680000,"text":"Used to be, there were two mustards:\nFrench's and Gulden's."},{"time":683225,"text":"What were they? Yellow mustard."},{"time":684742,"text":"What's in it?"},{"time":685781,"text":"Yellow mustard seeds,\nturmeric, and paprika."},{"time":687859,"text":"That was mustard."},{"time":688957,"text":"Grey Poupon came along, with a Dijon."},{"time":691506,"text":"Right?"},{"time":692718,"text":"Much more volatile brown mustard seed,\nsome white wine, a nose hit,"},{"time":698405,"text":"much more delicate aromatics."},{"time":700367,"text":"And what do they do?"},{"time":701406,"text":"They put it in a little tiny glass jar,\nwith a wonderful enameled label on it,"},{"time":706229,"text":"made it look French,"},{"time":707327,"text":"even though it's made\nin Oxnard, California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709452,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":710477,"text":"And instead of charging a dollar fifty\nfor the eight-ounce bottle,"},{"time":715000,"text":"the way that French's and Gulden's did,"},{"time":716997,"text":"they decided to charge four dollars."},{"time":718748,"text":"And they had those ads."},{"time":719984,"text":"With the guy in the Rolls Royce,\neating the Grey Poupon."},{"time":722643,"text":"Another pulls up, and says,\n\"Do you have any Grey Poupon?\""},{"time":725453,"text":"And the whole thing, after they did that,\nGrey Poupon takes off!"},{"time":728661,"text":"Takes over the mustard business!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":730209,"text":"And everyone's take-home lesson from that"},{"time":732241,"text":"was that the way to make people happy"},{"time":737000,"text":"is to give them something\nthat is more expensive,"},{"time":740418,"text":"something to aspire to."},{"time":742509,"text":"It's to make them turn their back\non what they think they like now,"},{"time":746676,"text":"and reach out for something\nhigher up the mustard hierarchy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750119,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":751144,"text":"A better mustard!\nA more expensive mustard!"},{"time":753380,"text":"A mustard of more sophistication\nand culture and meaning."},{"time":756567,"text":"And Howard looked to that\nand said, \"That's wrong!\""},{"time":759639,"text":"Mustard does not exist on a hierarchy."},{"time":762218,"text":"Mustard exists, just like tomato sauce,\non a horizontal plane."},{"time":766779,"text":"There is no good mustard or bad mustard."},{"time":769542,"text":"There is no perfect mustard\nor imperfect mustard."},{"time":772092,"text":"There are only different kinds of mustards\nthat suit different kinds of people."},{"time":776358,"text":"He fundamentally democratized\nthe way we think about taste."},{"time":781217,"text":"And for that, as well, we owe\nHoward Moskowitz a huge vote of thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786201,"text":"Third thing that Howard did,\nand perhaps the most important,"},{"time":789718,"text":"is Howard confronted the notion\nof the Platonic dish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792581,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":793606,"text":"What do I mean by that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794772,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":796352,"text":"For the longest time in the food industry,"},{"time":798476,"text":"there was a sense that there was one way,"},{"time":801080,"text":"a perfect way, to make a dish."},{"time":804570,"text":"You go to Chez Panisse,"},{"time":806309,"text":"they give you the red-tail sashimi\nwith roasted pumpkin seeds"},{"time":811616,"text":"in a something something reduction."},{"time":813493,"text":"They don't give you five options\non the reduction."},{"time":816000,"text":"They don't say, \"Do you want\nthe extra-chunky reduction, or ...?\""},{"time":819618,"text":"No!"},{"time":820650,"text":"You just get the reduction. Why?"},{"time":822221,"text":"Because the chef at Chez Panisse"},{"time":823807,"text":"has a Platonic notion\nabout red-tail sashimi."},{"time":826419,"text":"\"This is the way it ought to be.\""},{"time":828920,"text":"And she serves it that way\ntime and time again,"},{"time":833000,"text":"and if you quarrel with her, she will say,"},{"time":835286,"text":"\"You know what? You're wrong!"},{"time":837468,"text":"This is the best way it ought to be\nin this restaurant.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":840212,"text":"Now that same idea fueled\nthe commercial food industry as well."},{"time":844294,"text":"They had a Platonic notion\nof what tomato sauce was."},{"time":847535,"text":"And where did that come from?\nIt came from Italy."},{"time":850000,"text":"Italian tomato sauce is what?"},{"time":852375,"text":"It's blended; it's thin."},{"time":854531,"text":"The culture of tomato sauce was thin."},{"time":856864,"text":"When we talked about \"authentic\ntomato sauce\" in the 1970s,"},{"time":859865,"text":"we talked about Italian tomato sauce,"},{"time":861698,"text":"we talked about the earliest Ragùs,"},{"time":863501,"text":"which had no visible solids, right?"},{"time":866000,"text":"Which were thin, you just put a little bit"},{"time":868141,"text":"and it sunk down to the bottom\nof the pasta."},{"time":870213,"text":"That's what it was."},{"time":871429,"text":"And why were we attached to that?"},{"time":873114,"text":"Because we thought\nthat what it took to make people happy"},{"time":875876,"text":"was to provide them with the most\nculturally authentic tomato sauce, A."},{"time":880494,"text":"And B, we thought that if we gave them\nthe culturally authentic tomato sauce,"},{"time":885602,"text":"then they would embrace it."},{"time":887054,"text":"And that's what would please\nthe maximum number of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890288,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":892598,"text":"people in the cooking world\nwere looking for cooking universals."},{"time":896336,"text":"They were looking for one way\nto treat all of us."},{"time":898798,"text":"And it's good reason for them\nto be obsessed"},{"time":901402,"text":"with the idea of universals,"},{"time":902808,"text":"because all of science,"},{"time":904229,"text":"through the 19th century\nand much of the 20th,"},{"time":906502,"text":"was obsessed with universals."},{"time":908195,"text":"Psychologists, medical scientists,\neconomists"},{"time":912207,"text":"were all interested\nin finding out the rules"},{"time":914319,"text":"that govern the way all of us behave."},{"time":917259,"text":"But that changed, right?"},{"time":918681,"text":"What is the great revolution\nin science of the last 10, 15 years?"},{"time":922316,"text":"It is the movement\nfrom the search for universals"},{"time":925855,"text":"to the understanding of variability."},{"time":928339,"text":"Now in medical science,\nwe don't want to know, necessarily,"},{"time":932000,"text":"just how cancer works,"},{"time":933725,"text":"we want to know how your cancer\nis different from my cancer."},{"time":937000,"text":"I guess my cancer different\nfrom your cancer."},{"time":939771,"text":"Genetics has opened the door\nto the study of human variability."},{"time":943883,"text":"What Howard Moskowitz\nwas doing was saying,"},{"time":946002,"text":"\"This same revolution needs to happen\nin the world of tomato sauce.\""},{"time":951000,"text":"And for that, we owe him\na great vote of thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955201,"text":"I'll give you one last\nillustration of variability,"},{"time":958067,"text":"and that is -- oh, I'm sorry."},{"time":959932,"text":"Howard not only believed that,\nbut he took it a second step,"},{"time":963444,"text":"which was to say that when we pursue\nuniversal principles in food,"},{"time":968620,"text":"we aren't just making an error;"},{"time":970264,"text":"we are actually doing ourselves\na massive disservice."},{"time":974000,"text":"And the example he used was coffee."},{"time":976223,"text":"And coffee is something he did\na lot of work with, with Nescafé."},{"time":980746,"text":"If I were to ask all of you to try\nand come up with a brand of coffee --"},{"time":984268,"text":"a type of coffee, a brew --\nthat made all of you happy,"},{"time":987314,"text":"and then I asked you to rate that coffee,"},{"time":989291,"text":"the average score in this room for coffee\nwould be about 60 on a scale of 0 to 100."},{"time":993825,"text":"If, however, you allowed me\nto break you into coffee clusters,"},{"time":997472,"text":"maybe three or four coffee clusters,"},{"time":999281,"text":"and I could make coffee just\nfor each of those individual clusters,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"your scores would go from 60 to 75 or 78."},{"time":1008000,"text":"The difference between coffee\nat 60 and coffee at 78"},{"time":1013261,"text":"is a difference between coffee\nthat makes you wince,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"and coffee that makes you\ndeliriously happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019690,"text":"That is the final, and I think\nmost beautiful lesson,"},{"time":1022908,"text":"of Howard Moskowitz:"},{"time":1024267,"text":"that in embracing the diversity\nof human beings,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"we will find a surer way\nto true happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030769,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031810,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}